          "text": [
            "<p><strong>Problem 3.2</strong></p><p><strong>Families of Facts: Division of Rational Numbers</strong></p><p>We know there is a relationship between addition and subtraction represented in fact families. A similar relationship exists between multiplication and division. For any multiplication fact, we can write another multiplication fact and two different related division positive number facts. The following are examples of fact families using multiplication and division.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
