      {
        "id": "1RrkgCyc_1n0q98Z",
        "title": "Text 3",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Each rational number has an additive inverse, a + (â€“a) = 0. Also, each rational number has a multiplicative inverse which is its <em>reciprocal</em>. A rational number and its reciprocal are called multiplicative inverses. Their product is 1. </p>"
          ]
        }
      },
